FBIS4-40723 "drsov118_d_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 Regional Affairs Russian Procurator Ilyushenko Visiting N. Caucasus Russian Procurator Ilyushenko Visiting N. Caucasus Announces Special Procuracy LD1706125994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0646 GMT 17 Jun 94 LD1706125994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] [Text] Vladikavkaz, 17 June -- A procuracy with special powers is to be set up in the state of emergency zone in North Caucasus. This was announced on 16 June by Aleksey Ilyushenko, acting Russian Federation procurator general, who is visiting Vladikavkaz. He said that this decision was made in order to ensure that laws are complied with and to coordinate the work of investigative bodies. Aleksey Ilyushenko is touring the North Caucasus in order to familiarize himself with the situation in the region and to prepare proposals for a meeting of the Russian Government which will examine progress in implementing Russian presidential edicts and cabinet decisions on the return of refugees to their former homes.
